    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p>
<ol class="HELM_parts">

<li><p>A box contains \({@aa@}\) bad tube(s) and \({@bb@}\) good tubes.&nbsp; Two are drawn out together.&nbsp; One of them is tested and found to be good.&nbsp; What is the probability that the other one is also good?</p> [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]<p></p></li>

<li><p></p><p>A man owns a house in town and a cottage in the country.&nbsp; In any one year the probability of the town house being burgled is \(\displaystyle{{@cc@}}\) and the probability of the country cottage being burgled is\(\displaystyle{{@dd@}}\).&nbsp; In any one year what is the probability that:</p> <p>(1) both will be burgled?[[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]]</p>
<p>(2) one or the other (but not both) will be burgled?[[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]] [[feedback:prt3]]</p></li><li><p>In a Baseball Series, teams \(A\) and \(B\) play until one team has won \({@ee@}\) games.&nbsp; If team \(A\) has probability \(\dfrac{2}{3}\) of winning against \(B\) in a single game, what is the probability that the Series will end only after \({@ff@}\) games are played?</p><p></p>[[input:ans4]] [[validation:ans4]] [[feedback:prt4]]</li></ol>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<ol class="HELM_parts"><p>
</p><li>Let \(G_i=\{i^{th} \text{ tube is good}\}\quad B_i=\{i^{th} \text{ tube is bad}\}\)<p></p><p>\(\text{P}(G_2|G_1)={@ta1@}\) (only \(({@bb@}-1)\) good tubes left out of \(9\)).</p></li><li><p>(1) \(H=\{\)house is burgled\(\}\ \ C=\{\)cottage is burgled\(\}\) 
\[\text{P}(H\cap C)=\text{P}(H)\text{P}(C)=\left({@cc@}\right)\left({@dd@}\right)={@ta21@}\] since events independent.<br><br>
(2) \[\text{P(one or the other (but not both))}=\text{P}((H\cap C')\cup (H' \cap C))=\text{P}(H\cap C')+\text{P}(H'\cap C)\]\[=\text{P}(H)\text{P}(C')+\text{P}(H')\text{P}(C)=\left({@cc@}\right)\left({@ndd@}\right)+\left({@ncc@}\right)\left({@dd@}\right)={@ta22@}.\]&nbsp;<br></p></li><li><p></p><p>Let \(A_i\) be event \(\{A\) wins the \(i^{th}\) game\(\}\). The required event is \(A\) winning \({@ee@}-1\) games and losing \({@gg@}\) games in any order.</p><p>\[\text{P(required event)}=\binom{{@ff@}-1}{{@ee@}-1}[\text{P}(A_1)]^{{@ee@}-1}[\text{P}(A'_1)]^{{@gg@}}={@ta3@}.\]</p></li></ol><p></p>]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
